Preheat your oven to 210 degrees. Cut the @potato{1} in half lengthways (no need to peel)
and then chop each half into wedges the size of your index finger. Pop your wedges on a
#baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Toss and then roast in your oven on the top shelf
for ~{30%minutes}. Turn after ~{15%minutes} to make sure they cook evenly.

Strip the @rosemary{1/4}(finely chopped) leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard
the stalks). In a #large bowl{}, mix your rosemary with a glug of oil and a good pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}. Add the @pork medallions{2} and stir well
to coat them. Keep to one side, allowing the flavours to infuse.

Cut the green leafy bits off the @cauliflower{1/2} and then cut it into florets (small trees).
Pop your florets on another baking tray, season with salt, drizzle over some @olive oil{1%tbsp}
and then roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}, until golden and charred
at the edges.

While your cauliflower and potato are roasting, heat a #large frying pan{} over a high heat
and add a splash of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Fry your pork for ~{5-6%mins} on each side until
cooked through.

> Tip: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Whilst your pork is cooking, make a dressing. Pop the @raisins{40} in a #bowl{} and add the
@red wine vinegar{1} and the @Dijon mustard{1/2}.

> Tip: Be careful the mustard is hot! Start with a little and add more later if you feel
> the dressing needs it!

Mix in the @honey{1} and the @olive oil{3} and then add a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Keep to
one side, we will dress your cauliflower with it later. Crumble the @mature cheddar cheese{30}.

When your pork is cooked, remove it from the pan and leave to rest on a #chopping board{}
for ~{2%mins}.

When your cauliflower is ready, remove from your oven and toss it in your dressing. Divide
the @baby watercress{1} between your #plates{}. Nestle your wedges amongst the watercress
and then top with your roasted cauliflower. Slice your pork into five slices and place in
the centre of your plates. Drizzle over any remaining dressing and finish with your cheese.
Enjoy!